CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 11, 1965, pg. 6, reads: "Lifetime Members - The Gould Singers, who celebrated their 11th Anniversary recently made the final payment of their 'Life Membership' in NAACP with proceeds received from the anniversary program. Mrs. Ruby Gould, directress presents a check for $425 to Attorney Byrd R. Brown, president of the Pittsburgh NAACP.  Seated from left to right: Constance McPherson, Naomi Porter, Carrie Green.  Standing left to right: Ethel Kindred, Lois Francis, Ruby Gould, Byrd R. Brown, Mary White, Evelyn Zellous.  Second row, from left to right--Rhetta Givner, Ethel Parrott, Mildred Crawford, Willa Chandler, Florence Davis, Helen Clark.  Back row, from left--Jemmie Hatcher, Katherine Earl, Erma Neason, Rosanne Hatcher. (Harris Photo)"
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of the Gould Singers, seated left to right: Constance McPherson, Naomi Porter, Carrie Green; standing first row: Ethel Kindred, Lois Francis, Ruby Gould presenting NAACP lifetime membership check to Byrd R. Brown, Mary White, Evelyn Zellous; second row: Rhetta Givner, Ethel Parrott, Mildred Crawford, Willa "Kitty" Warren Chandler, Florence Davis, Helen Clark: third row: Jemmie Hatcher, Katherine Earl, Erma Neason, Rosanne Hatcher
